<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="small-adj">small <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /smɔːl/    美 /smɔːl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>小的；(数量) 少的；(字母) 小写的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a small town
小镇</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a small sum of money
一小笔钱</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>small letters
小写字母</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>幼小的；矮小的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A small woman in her eighties stood before me.
一个八十多岁的矮个子女人站在我面前。</p><footer>2008 北京</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(规模、价值、程度等) 小型的；微不足道的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>small talk</strong>
聊天；闲聊</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a small matter
小事</p></div></div>